TYPE="PERDOC"
SIZE="100"
DOCREF="AP890930-0100"
SELECTOR="A"
SUMMARIZER="E">    

Chicago had undergone two days of hearings on police brutality by 30
September 1989.  A report describing widespread segregation shows that
much work remains to be done on race relations.

The mayor, Richard M. Daley, son of Mayor Richard J. Daley who ruled
Chicago as mayor for 20 years until 1976, was elected to office
promising empowerment to minorities.  He gave 11 of 21 cabinet posts
to minorities.  Blacks charge the police force with brutality,
intimidation, beatings and false arrests.  Lack of contact among the
city's ethnic groups may be one cause.  The black police chief faulted
himself for any failures.</SUM>

<SUM
DOCSET="d06"
TYPE="PERDOC"
SIZE="100"
DOCREF="AP890322-0010"
SELECTOR="A"
SUMMARIZER="E">    

Police brutality and racism are terms not usually applied to the
Minneapolis Police Department.  The city prides itself on its
tolerance.

That was not the case during a recent drug raid when two blacks died
and later during a confrontation between blacks and police.

Protesters demanded that the officers involved be suspended and are
calling for a police review board, which the police chief opposes.

A city official stated that police racism has existed for over 21
years despite the public impression of tolerance.

The chief of police said cultural awareness training for his force
would begin in the fall.</SUM>

<SUM
DOCSET="d06"
TYPE="PERDOC"
SIZE="100"
DOCREF="AP901029-0035"
SELECTOR="A"
SUMMARIZER="E">    

Terry Barnes, a 24-year old stockbroker, was shot and killed by police
in his own apartment.  It was another blow against the Kansas City,
Missouri Police Department struggling against charges of racism and
brutality.  Both the victim and the officer are white, although other
incidents have involved black citizens.
  
Other charges against the police have included excessive force and
racism.  One involved a black Roman Catholic priest from Nigeria who
was attacked by police while laying on the ground.  The priest said
officers stopped him on suspicion of drunken driving because they
could not understand his foreign speech.</SUM>

<SUM
